#: scripts/science_db.lua:75
msgid ""
"Whether your mission involves scientific investigation, deep-space "
"exploration, or military operations, remember to take advantage of any scan "
"probes distributed for your ship.\n"
"\n"
"Your Relay officer can launch a probe to any coordinates in their sector "
"map, which fires its payload at high velocity directly toward the target "
"coordinates. Upon arrival, Relay can then link the probe to the Science "
"officer, who can switch their long-range radar to the probe's short-range "
"radar.\n"
"\n"
"This allows the Science officer to scan objects well outside of your ship's "
"long-range radar range, including regions obfuscated by phenomena like "
"nebulae that occlude your sensors.\n"
"\n"
"Scan probes have a limited energy supply and expire within minutes, and your "
"ship carries a limited number of them that only some stations can or will "
"replenish."
msgstr ""

